50|$|The Stepney Tenants’ Defence League was {{organised}} by the Communist Front {{and women}} chaired {{most of the}} tenants’ committees formed in tenement blocks, organised opposition to attempted evictions attempts, and even demonstrated in the West End of London to highlight the plight of east London slum-dwellers.In 1938 the <b>decontrol</b> <b>of</b> much housing {{in the area and}} proposed rent increases of up to 40% led to STDL becoming even more active, and Ella Donovan, the wife of an unemployed hall porter, became a full-time organizer. This was a time when women who previously had not been engaged in activism, ‘lost their fear of the landlord and learnt their own organized power’ in Ella’s own words.|$|R
